�ҵ{�W���ƭȰ��L����{(�@)Numerical Analysis for Partial Differential Equations I
�ҵ{²�����ҵ{���ƭȰ��L����{���J���ҵ{�C�D�n�b�оɾǥͦp��o�i�����t���k�ﰾ�L����{�D�ѡA�P�ɤ��R�ƭȤ�k��í�w�ʻP���ĩʡC���ҵ{���N�б¦����t���k�ѦU�ؤ��P�������D�]�t�G����{���D�B�X����{���D�B��y��{���D�CThis course provides an introduction to solve partial differential equations numerically. The course covers the finite difference approximation, elliptic equations, Fourier analysis of linear PDEs, diffusion equations, advection equations.





�ҵ{�W���ƭȰ��L����{(�G)Numerical Analysis for Partial Differential Equations II
�ҵ{²�����ҵ{���ƭȰ��L����{���i���ҵ{�C�D�n�b�оɾǥͦp��]�p�o�i���������k�B������n�k�άO��ɤ����k��S�w�������L����{�D�ѡA�P�ɤ��R�ƭȤ�k��í�w�ʻP���ĩʡCThis course is an advanced course for numerical partial differential equations. The course aims to provide students with understanding of solving partial differential equations with finite element methods, finite volume methods or boundary elements.





�ҵ{�W���ƭȽu�ʥN��Numerical Linear Algebra
�ҵ{²�����ҵ{���ت��O�ǲ߼ƭȽu�ʥN�ƪ��@�ǰ򥻪��ѡA�S�O�O�u�ʨt�Ϊ��ƭȸѺ⾹�M�̤p�G�����D�C�ҵ{���e�]�A�F�򥻪��x�}���R�A�u�ʨt�Ϊ��ӷP�ʤ��R�A�@��u�ʨt�Ϊ�LU���ѡA�������h�k�M�ǽT�ʤ��R�A����ƩM�̤p�G�����D�����N�ץ��A�u�ʨt�Ϊ��ƭȭ��N�Ѫk�G�зǤ������N�k�AJacobi�MGauss-Seidel��k�ASOR�PKrylov�k�CThe purpose of this course is to learn some elementary knowledge related to the numerical linear algebra, especially, numerical solvers for the linear systems and least squares problems. The course covers basic matrix analysis, sensitivity analysis of linear systems, LU factorization and general linear systems, Gaussian elimination and iterative refinement for accuracy, orthogonalization and least squares problems, iterative methods for linear systems: standard splitting iteration, Jacobi and Gauss-Seidel methods, SOR and Krylov-based methods.





